      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HANDS ON TINA (8) turned in a fair 4th placed finish last time at this track over 388m (22.79). Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Key runner on his best form. ZIPPING GOOFY (4) delivered a moderate run last time when sixth at The Gardens over 400m behind Us Two Boys (23.95). Form from his last run is proving strong. Likely to be about the mark. ALL MINE HONEY (2) pinged the lids and was in the firing line early but drifted out of it when 6th at Richmond in Maiden company. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. In the mix. BIGBAD EDEN (1) makes debut for the Joanne Brown kennel. Gets every chance from the inside draw. Expected to produce a bold debut.",
